<i>-Police are asking cooperation</i>
<i>of local residents.</i>
-Oh, my God!

27:24.150 --> 27:26.090
Did you say something?

27:26.090 --> 27:27.920
Listen, uh...

27:28.190 --> 27:32.120
Can you tell Kim
that I'll stop by later?

27:32.130 --> 27:35.230
I have to go.
[GASPING]

27:35.230 --> 27:35.890
Sorry.

27:35.900 --> 27:40.670
REPORTER:
<i>...and that's when police</i>
<i>discovered the mutilated body.</i>

27:44.210 --> 27:50.180
<i>Police conducted a thorough</i>
<i>search of the area in hopes</i>
<i>of finding the murder weapon.</i>

27:50.180 --> 27:52.540
<i>But so far,</i>
<i>it has not been found.</i>

27:52.550 --> 27:54.450
Can't be.
Can't be.

27:54.450 --> 27:58.220
REPORTER: <i> For reasons unknown,</i>
<i>Tebbs's foot was severed</i>
<i>from his body.</i>

27:58.220 --> 27:59.080
<i>It, too, has yet to be found.</i>

27:59.090 --> 28:06.160
<i>Police say they have no leads</i>
<i>on any suspects in connection</i>
<i>with Tebbs's gruesome murder.</i>

28:06.160 --> 28:09.760
<i>Mountview has never</i>
<i>been touched by</i>
<i>such a tragedy as this.</i>

28:09.770 --> 28:13.940
<i>Now come the questions</i>
<i>of who and why.</i>

28:13.940 --> 28:17.310
[SIREN WAILING]

28:17.310 --> 28:20.950
[CROWD CHATTERING]

28:48.640 --> 28:51.500
POLICEMAN:
Hey, kid.

28:51.840 --> 28:54.310
You following me?

28:54.310 --> 28:57.140
I... Listen, I can explain.

28:57.150 --> 28:58.120
Explain what?

28:58.120 --> 29:01.120
You don't have to
explain anything.

29:01.990 --> 29:03.590
Or do you?

29:03.590 --> 29:04.560
You're inside a police line.

29:04.560 --> 29:08.260
Now this is the second
time I'm telling you,
go home.

29:08.260 --> 29:09.690
Go.

29:17.030 --> 29:21.230
[WHIRRING ELECTRONIC SOUNDS]

29:24.940 --> 29:29.410
VOICE FROM BRAINSCAN:
<i>Be sure you put it</i>
<i>in a safe place.</i>

29:29.410 --> 29:33.550
[WHIRRING ELECTRONIC SOUNDS
CONTINUE]

29:41.160 --> 29:42.490
[GASPS]

29:46.960 --> 29:49.900
OPERATOR:
<i>I'm sorry, sir,</i>
<i>there's no such number listed.</i>

29:49.900 --> 29:54.270
-[SHOUTING]
That's impossible!
<i>-I'm sorry, sir.</i>

29:54.270 --> 29:55.770
[PHONE RINGING]

29:55.770 --> 29:59.340
<i>You have a call, Master.</i>

29:59.340 --> 30:02.010
[ZAPPING]

30:05.650 --> 30:07.450
VOICE FROM BRAINSCAN:
<i>Hello, Michael.</i>

30:07.450 --> 30:09.780
You sucker! Who are you?
What did you do?

30:09.790 --> 30:12.630
<i>If I were you, I would</i>
<i>address that question</i>
<i>to myself.</i>

30:12.620 --> 30:16.050
Okay, who killed that man,
and what's happened?

30:16.060 --> 30:19.630
<i>You were there, Michael.</i>
<i>You know exactly what you did.</i>

30:19.630 --> 30:23.030
[GLASS CRACKING]

30:43.820 --> 30:49.990
Please allow me
to introduce myself.
My name is Trickster.

30:52.800 --> 30:58.340
Where were we?
Ah, yes.

30:58.340 --> 31:00.410
You may not
remember the details, my boy,

31:00.400 --> 31:04.500
but I am positive you remember
you controlled the disk.

31:04.510 --> 31:08.240
-You controlled
what happened.
-What?

31:08.250 --> 31:10.950
So you take responsibility.

31:10.950 --> 31:13.110
How did you get
in here?

31:13.780 --> 31:15.780
You invited me in.

31:15.790 --> 31:17.930
That's how
it always works.

31:17.920 --> 31:22.820
Michael, don't you
have anything good?

31:27.460 --> 31:31.000
Never leave home
without it.

31:33.670 --> 31:36.370
From the top
of the charts...

31:36.370 --> 31:40.110
To a space
in your heart.

31:41.510 --> 31:43.840
[SCREAMS]

31:43.850 --> 31:46.820
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

31:51.560 --> 31:53.500
MICHAEL:
Stop that! Stop it!

31:53.490 --> 31:58.720
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

32:01.830 --> 32:04.600
[STOPS MUSIC]
Knock it off!

32:07.670 --> 32:09.170
So you did it.

32:09.170 --> 32:13.240
Who killed that man?
What was on that disk?

32:13.240 --> 32:14.510
The murder.
What else?

32:14.510 --> 32:17.780
You know for a minute there,
I didn't think
you'd go through with it.

32:17.780 --> 32:22.750
When he got up
and started dancing
around the room...

32:22.750 --> 32:24.680
Classic.

32:24.690 --> 32:25.220
How do you know?

32:25.220 --> 32:29.860
I was there
when you cut off his foot.
It was art. It was magic.

32:29.860 --> 32:31.490
It wasn't
supposed to be real!

32:31.500 --> 32:35.900
Real. Unreal.
What's the difference? So long
as you don't get caught.

32:35.900 --> 32:41.330
There's a difference, okay?
There's a big difference!
This doesn't make any sense!

32:41.340 --> 32:46.270
It doesn't have to make sense.
All these horror movies
you watch...

32:46.280 --> 32:48.750
Does "Death, Death, Death"
make sense?

32:48.750 --> 32:54.060
No. It's not about sense.
It's about death, death,
death.

32:54.050 --> 32:56.720
I didn't kill the man.
I didn't even know him!

32:56.720 --> 32:58.680
There lies the beauty.

32:58.690 --> 33:01.650
You had no motive.
It was totally random.

33:01.660 --> 33:06.360
Like in the animal world,
prey never has a name.

33:06.360 --> 33:07.690
It was primal.

33:07.700 --> 33:10.140
[GROWLS]

33:10.130 --> 33:14.930
I can't wait to see
what you do next.

33:14.940 --> 33:19.870
Next? Wait a minute!
There is no next.

33:20.810 --> 33:22.210
Yes, there is.

33:22.210 --> 33:23.710
No, there's not!

33:23.710 --> 33:25.640
Yes, there is!

33:25.750 --> 33:29.180
You must
eliminate the witness.

33:30.650 --> 33:32.620
There was a witness?

33:32.620 --> 33:35.450
Two, if you count me.

33:35.460 --> 33:37.260
But I'll never
turn you in.

33:37.260 --> 33:40.490
They could
pump a million volts
through me.

33:40.500 --> 33:42.900
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

33:47.300 --> 33:53.340
They could bust my fingers,
one by one,

33:53.340 --> 33:55.240
by one,

33:55.250 --> 33:56.650
by one.

33:56.650 --> 34:00.090
They could dig out my eyes...

34:00.080 --> 34:02.410
[SQUELCHING]

34:11.659 --> 34:12.620
But...

34:12.630 --> 34:18.929
No country-western music,
please. Every man
has his limits.

34:19.340 --> 34:24.179
I thought it was just a game.
You know, a stupid video game.

34:24.170 --> 34:26.610
Trust me.
Play the second disk.

34:26.610 --> 34:29.770
-How could there
be a witness?
-Oh, come on, sport.

34:29.780 --> 34:33.580
You're more than just the
voyeur you wish to be,
you're in this now.

34:33.580 --> 34:37.719
You won't survive on your own.
I'm willing to help you.

34:37.719 --> 34:39.889
But you have to play
all the disks.

34:39.889 --> 34:43.560
Hey, I've done
pretty good so far.

34:43.560 --> 34:46.560
Have you?
[ZAPPING]

34:59.880 --> 35:03.020
I'm in deep stuff.

35:55.600 --> 35:57.860
[WHINES]

36:03.370 --> 36:04.970
Oh, God.

36:06.840 --> 36:09.040
[GROWLS]

36:09.450 --> 36:11.550
Here, boy,
come on.

36:11.550 --> 36:16.050
-[GROWLS]
-Here, boy,
come on.

36:17.020 --> 36:18.220
Come on.

36:18.220 --> 36:19.750
[PERSON WHISTLES]

36:19.760 --> 36:21.730
Hey, wait a minute!

36:22.630 --> 36:24.930
[PANTING]

36:34.070 --> 36:37.100
Shoot!
[PANTING]

36:45.520 --> 36:49.560
Hey. Hey.
I know you're a nice dog.

36:49.550 --> 36:53.220
Please, please
give me the foot.

36:53.220 --> 37:00.130
Okay?
I promise, I'll never ask you
for anything else again. Okay?

37:00.130 --> 37:02.190
Just give me the foot.

37:02.200 --> 37:03.900
[WHINES]

37:03.900 --> 37:06.770
[SIGHS IN RELIEF]
Thanks!

37:10.340 --> 37:13.170
[BARKING]

37:16.010 --> 37:19.380
[INSECT BUZZING]

37:26.720 --> 37:29.450
[GROANS]

37:31.160 --> 37:32.960
What do you got there?

37:35.000 --> 37:37.200
What are you looking at?

37:40.370 --> 37:41.930
Come on, Zak.

37:41.940 --> 37:43.800
Get outta here.

38:01.290 --> 38:03.860
KYLE: Hey, dude.
[DOORBELL RINGING]

38:03.860 --> 38:05.990
[POUNDING ON DOOR]

38:09.970 --> 38:13.380
[POUNDING CONTINUES]

38:14.740 --> 38:18.970
Hey!
Yo, Michael.

38:22.280 --> 38:27.650
Hey, dirtbag,
I've been callin' all day.
Did you skip school?

38:27.650 --> 38:31.580
Uh, no, I...
I got mono.

38:31.590 --> 38:34.820
That's harsh.
Anything I can do?

38:34.820 --> 38:36.150
Nah, that's all right.

38:36.160 --> 38:37.760
Can I come in?

38:37.990 --> 38:42.490
Kyle, I don't think
it's such a good idea
right now.

38:42.900 --> 38:43.600
Okay, okay.

38:43.600 --> 38:46.460
Listen, I have to get goin'.
I have to go to bed
and all, you know...

38:46.470 --> 38:50.340
-Hey, did ya hear
about the murder?
-Yeah, I did.

38:50.340 --> 38:54.970
Yeah, that's pretty cool
havin' a murder in our own
neighborhood and everything.

38:54.980 --> 38:58.480
Kyle, a guy just died,
and you think that's cool?

38:58.480 --> 39:01.950
No, I don't mean cool,
but it's interesting.

39:01.950 --> 39:02.810
Forget it!
I'll see you.

39:02.820 --> 39:07.190
Hey, listen Michael, if you're
gonna be laid up, how 'bout
letting me borrow Brainscan?

39:07.190 --> 39:10.690
Kyle, idiot, will you
get off my back about that?

39:10.690 --> 39:12.990
No, no. If you don't wanna
let me see it,

39:13.000 --> 39:14.670
if you just want
to be a jerk about it,

39:14.660 --> 39:18.660
-just say so,
that's all!
-Bye, Kyle.

39:19.770 --> 39:22.230
[RINGING DOORBELL]

39:29.510 --> 39:31.410
You, too.

39:34.650 --> 39:38.680
[HEAVY METAL MUSIC PLAYING]

39:39.890 --> 39:42.350
<i>♪ Shouldn't have to be</i>
<i>like this</i>

39:42.360 --> 39:45.860
<i>♪ Shouldn't have to be</i>
<i>like this</i>

39:50.070 --> 39:52.610
<i>♪ Shouldn't have to be</i>
<i>like this</i>

39:52.600 --> 39:56.300
<i>♪ Shouldn't have to be</i>
<i>like this  ♪</i>

39:57.110 --> 39:59.480
[DOORBELL RINGING]

40:06.380 --> 40:08.450
[RINGING CONTINUES]

40:08.450 --> 40:10.580
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

40:12.590 --> 40:13.990
Jeez!

40:18.090 --> 40:19.760
[EXHALES]

40:25.440 --> 40:27.480
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

40:27.470 --> 40:28.530
Hey.
Hi, Michael.

40:28.540 --> 40:31.440
I'm sorry,
were you sleeping?

40:31.440 --> 40:35.440
Well, actually, maybe
I may have dozed off.

40:35.450 --> 40:37.650
Can I come in?

40:37.650 --> 40:40.590
Oh, yeah, I'm sorry.

40:44.490 --> 40:47.960
KIMBERLY: Yeah, they're
all over the neighborhood.

40:49.290 --> 40:53.930
I, uh, went to all your
teachers, and I got your
homework for the week.

40:53.930 --> 40:57.960
Oh, thanks.

40:59.640 --> 41:02.310
My parents said
you stopped by?

41:02.310 --> 41:03.850
Yeah, I did.

41:03.840 --> 41:07.140
I just wanted to find out
about some homework.

41:07.140 --> 41:10.740
We don't have
any classes together,
Michael.

41:10.750 --> 41:14.420
Oh, we don't, do we?

41:15.180 --> 41:17.250
Oh, here's your mail.

41:17.250 --> 41:17.850
Oh, thanks.

41:17.850 --> 41:23.020
And I brought <i> The Montie.</i>
I have a lot of pictures
in it this week.

41:23.030 --> 41:24.500
Oh.

41:26.460 --> 41:28.090
That's, uh...

41:29.330 --> 41:31.260
That's really nice.

41:31.270 --> 41:32.110
Uh...

41:32.100 --> 41:33.830
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

41:34.870 --> 41:40.440
Damn! Wait a minute.
Sorry, I got it, I got it.
Thanks a lot.

41:40.440 --> 41:42.340
[PANTING]

41:43.280 --> 41:45.610
Is everything okay?

41:47.920 --> 41:50.660
You should
probably get going.

41:50.650 --> 41:56.390
Oh, okay... I'll, um...
Let myself out.

42:01.800 --> 42:04.600
Thanks for stoppin' by.

42:05.230 --> 42:07.700
Call me if you need anything.

42:08.170 --> 42:11.170
Yeah, I will.

42:15.210 --> 42:17.140
Jeez!

42:39.270 --> 42:40.400
[RINGING]

42:40.400 --> 42:41.970
IGOR: <i> Telephone, Master.</i>

42:41.970 --> 42:44.340
[RINGING CONTINUES]

42:44.340 --> 42:45.640
Talk to me.

42:45.640 --> 42:47.610
<i>You have a call, Master.</i>

42:47.610 --> 42:51.440
[ZAPPING]

42:54.880 --> 42:56.610
I'm back.

42:56.620 --> 42:58.420
Well, pal, so glad
to see you again.

42:58.420 --> 43:03.050
-Where should we begin?
Where's the second disk?
-I can't play it.

43:03.060 --> 43:04.690
You have to play the game.

43:04.690 --> 43:05.190
No!

43:05.190 --> 43:08.960
-What will you say
to them, then?
-What do you mean?

43:08.970 --> 43:10.870
Why did you leave school
the day of the murder,
Mr. Brower?

43:10.870 --> 43:14.240
Where were you
the night of the murder?
Were you alone, Mr. Brower?

43:14.240 --> 43:18.150
Where's your father,
Mr. Brower? Where's
your mother, Mr. Brower?

43:18.140 --> 43:18.540
Shut up!

43:18.540 --> 43:20.610
Oh, I don't believe
they'll find that answer
satisfactory.

43:20.610 --> 43:23.880
-They haven't found me yet!
-The witness has yet to
speak.

43:23.880 --> 43:26.340
-There's still time
to play the second disk.
-Look!

43:26.350 --> 43:27.880
I don't have the
second disk!

43:27.880 --> 43:31.780
Don't lie to me, Michael.
You received it today.

43:31.790 --> 43:34.720
-Can't play it!
-You mean you don't
want to play it.

43:34.720 --> 43:37.120
No! I trashed it.
Does that compute?

43:37.130 --> 43:43.370
-Pure fantasy.
You did nothing of the sort.
-[WHIRRING]

43:49.040 --> 43:50.870
Play it.

43:51.270 --> 43:53.770
The witness has to die.

43:54.210 --> 43:56.210
I'll play it
for the police.

43:56.210 --> 43:58.040
That could be
very dangerous.

43:58.050 --> 44:01.820
I'll tell them what happened.
I've got nothing to lose.

44:02.120 --> 44:04.220
Very well,

44:04.220 --> 44:07.720
play it for the police.

44:07.720 --> 44:10.290
I wish you luck.

44:10.290 --> 44:12.790
Shut up, all right!
Just shut up a minute!

44:12.800 --> 44:17.070
The real question is
are you a winner or a loser?

44:20.500 --> 44:23.840
[ZAPPING]

44:26.440 --> 44:30.710
<i>My name's Michael Brower.</i>
<i>I'm 16, and I'm scared</i>
<i>to death.</i>

44:30.710 --> 44:32.910
<i>I'm not sure</i>
<i>what this tape's gonna prove,</i>

44:32.920 --> 44:37.460
<i>but if I'm the killer,</i>
<i>consider this my confession.</i>

44:39.690 --> 44:43.790
<i>Uh, Igor, dial 1-800-555-FEAR.</i>

44:43.790 --> 44:45.020
<i>IGOR: Yes, Master.</i>

44:45.030 --> 44:46.030
[DIALING]

44:46.030 --> 44:50.090
<i>Well, here goes nothing.</i>

44:51.170 --> 44:54.480
[ZAPPING]

45:02.380 --> 45:05.480
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

45:24.600 --> 45:28.100
[PANTING]

45:29.510 --> 45:32.010
Oh, jeez!

45:42.020 --> 45:43.850
Oh, God, I played.

45:43.850 --> 45:47.620
I played.
What happened?

45:54.430 --> 45:58.660
<i>My name's Michael Brower.</i>
<i>I'm 16, and I'm scared</i>
<i>to death.</i>

45:58.670 --> 46:00.970
<i>I'm not sure what this tape's</i>
<i>gonna prove,</i>

46:00.970 --> 46:05.840
<i>but if I'm the killer,</i>
<i>consider this my confession.</i>

46:07.480 --> 46:10.250
<i>Igor, dial 1-800-555-FEAR.</i>

46:10.250 --> 46:12.550
[DIALING]
<i>IGOR: Yes, Master.</i>

46:12.550 --> 46:16.310
MICHAEL:
<i>Well, here goes nothing.</i>

46:17.950 --> 46:21.490
[ZAPPING]

46:33.100 --> 46:35.700
What? What?

46:35.710 --> 46:38.380
Wait a minute!
I sat there!

46:38.370 --> 46:42.070
I swear to God
I didn't leave.

46:42.550 --> 46:47.660
[BUZZING]

46:55.060 --> 46:59.670
[BUZZING INCREASES]

47:07.570 --> 47:09.430
Kyle!

47:16.210 --> 47:20.040
No!
Not this.

47:24.650 --> 47:25.950
Dial Kyle!

47:25.960 --> 47:27.060
<i>Yes, Master.</i>

47:27.060 --> 47:28.830
[DIALING, RINGING]

47:28.820 --> 47:33.860
Please answer!
Kyle, please,
Kyle, answer!

47:35.230 --> 47:37.830
[RINGING]

47:39.240 --> 47:42.140
[RINGING CONTINUES]

47:44.470 --> 47:47.540
MICHAEL:
<i>Oh, man, Kyle, talk to me.</i>

47:47.540 --> 47:49.970
Kyle, please!

47:50.350 --> 47:53.450
POLICEMAN:
Who is this?

47:57.920 --> 48:00.180
Answer me.

48:02.490 --> 48:05.090
[HANGS UP]
Later.

48:21.240 --> 48:24.240
[PANTING]

48:31.350 --> 48:34.990
[DOORBELL RINGING]

48:39.400 --> 48:41.070
Hi.

48:44.970 --> 48:46.470
I heard.

48:52.410 --> 48:54.310
Michael.

49:01.450 --> 49:04.650
I really didn't know him,

49:05.290 --> 49:07.160
but, um,

49:07.160 --> 49:11.770
Kyle came to my house
last night.

49:11.760 --> 49:13.790
He brought me this.

49:13.800 --> 49:17.340
He started a petition
to restart the Horror Club.

49:17.330 --> 49:24.370
He said you guys had had
a fight, and he wanted me
to bring it to you personally.

49:27.010 --> 49:33.310
I really didn't know him.
My dad didn't wanna let him
in the house.

49:33.320 --> 49:35.290
Yeah.

49:35.280 --> 49:38.250
That's Kyle.

49:39.060 --> 49:43.760
You know...
I already miss him.

49:46.100 --> 49:48.640
-God, I miss him.
-REPORTER: <i> Mountview was</i>
<i>horrified today by the news</i>

49:48.630 --> 49:52.430
<i>of yet another</i>
<i>hideous crime committed</i>
<i>in their small community.</i>

49:52.440 --> 49:57.310
<i>High school student,</i>
<i>Kyle Hillard,</i>
<i>is the second murder victim</i>

49:57.310 --> 49:58.810
<i>in as little as three days.</i>

49:58.810 --> 50:00.770
<i>Shortly after Hillard's body</i>
<i>was identified,</i>

50:00.780 --> 50:05.820
<i>chief homicide investigator</i>
<i>Lieutenant Hayden arrived</i>
<i>at Mountview High</i>

50:05.820 --> 50:08.860
<i>to question those known</i>
<i>to have been</i>
<i>closest to the victim.</i>

50:08.850 --> 50:13.850
<i>Already, residents</i>
<i>are fearing the possibility</i>
<i>of a serial killer.</i>

50:13.860 --> 50:18.370
ON-SCENE REPORTER:
<i>Any foul play suspected?</i>

50:19.360 --> 50:20.990
Hello, Michael.

50:21.000 --> 50:23.300
You son of a gun,
you killed Kyle!

50:23.300 --> 50:29.170
No, you killed the witness.
[TURNS OFF TV]

50:29.170 --> 50:33.970
Kyle wasn't a witness!
He didn't even see anything.

50:33.980 --> 50:36.120
Not a witness
in the strictest sense,

50:36.110 --> 50:40.040
but he knew things
about you.

50:41.350 --> 50:42.710
Kyle was
my only friend!

50:42.720 --> 50:46.980
And you ticked him off!
Nice going, Michael.

50:47.190 --> 50:49.250
Got anything to eat?

50:52.730 --> 50:54.460
Please.

50:55.400 --> 50:57.910
Don't look in there.

51:02.340 --> 51:05.040
Don't be afraid, Michael.

51:05.040 --> 51:08.710
Nothing in there
but frozen meat.

51:11.110 --> 51:13.340
Loose ends like Kyle
can't be left to dangle.

51:13.350 --> 51:17.680
-Hayden would have tied it
around your neck like a noose.
-Why are you doing this?

51:17.690 --> 51:21.730
You chose me, Michael.
I didn't choose you.

51:21.720 --> 51:26.420
You left a clue behind...
In the second disk.

51:26.660 --> 51:28.330
No more games.

51:28.330 --> 51:29.530
I know.

51:29.530 --> 51:34.270
Kyle's death still hurts,
but do you really feel guilty
for what you've done?

51:34.270 --> 51:38.370
The part of you which did
these things,
It's deep inside,

51:38.370 --> 51:40.470
and it's in everyone.

51:40.480 --> 51:41.720
Be honest.

51:41.710 --> 51:47.010
If you don't feel the guilt,
why accept the punishment?

51:49.390 --> 51:51.990
[DOORBELL RINGS]

51:51.990 --> 51:53.160
Don't answer that.

51:53.160 --> 51:59.030
Trust me, Michael.
If you want this to end,
don't answer the door.

51:59.030 --> 52:00.760
[RINGING CONTINUES]

52:00.760 --> 52:02.630
Get off my back.

52:19.450 --> 52:21.210
[TURNS ON TV]

52:21.220 --> 52:23.290
LARRY: A tarantula!

52:23.290 --> 52:25.430
[SCREAMS]

52:25.420 --> 52:29.220
CURLEY:
Woo-woo-woo-woo!

52:32.730 --> 52:38.400
Hello. I'm Lieutenant Hayden.
This is my partner,
Sergeant Martin.

52:38.400 --> 52:40.660
We've met before.
Twice, I believe.

52:40.670 --> 52:46.370
Yeah, yeah, I know.
Um, can I help you?

52:46.380 --> 52:50.380
Yes, you can help me.
Michael? Michael Brower?

52:50.380 --> 52:51.640
Yeah.

52:51.650 --> 52:53.190
May we come in?

52:53.180 --> 52:55.780
Yeah, I guess so.

53:01.260 --> 53:05.300
Um, yeah, come this way.

53:14.700 --> 53:17.430
You haven't been
in school lately.

53:17.440 --> 53:19.300
No, I haven't.
I've been sick.

53:19.310 --> 53:22.510
Sorry to hear that.
I really am.

53:22.510 --> 53:25.240
We heard a lot
about you today
from your classmates.

53:25.250 --> 53:28.890
Really? Well,
I hope good stuff.

53:28.880 --> 53:32.350
Well, no.
To be perfectly frank,
Michael,

53:32.350 --> 53:35.690
you were described as, uh...

53:35.690 --> 53:38.120
What was the word they used,
Sergeant?

53:38.130 --> 53:44.200
-Frightening.
-HAYDEN: Frightening
and strange and weird.

53:44.200 --> 53:47.100
Freak came up
a couple a times.

53:47.100 --> 53:50.770
Sergeant Martin has something
I'd like you to see.

53:57.480 --> 54:00.310
MARTIN:
Good friend of yours?

54:02.350 --> 54:03.780
Yeah.

54:06.360 --> 54:09.130
Yeah, he was
my best friend.

54:09.120 --> 54:10.920
You don't have many friends,
do you, Michael?

54:10.930 --> 54:13.700
Listen,
is there anything
you guys want?

54:13.700 --> 54:15.700
We want to find the killer.

54:15.700 --> 54:18.160
I want to catch him.

54:18.170 --> 54:19.470
How do you spend
your free time, Michael?

54:19.470 --> 54:22.400
Just hanging around
and staying out of trouble.

54:22.400 --> 54:23.630
Your voice sounds
very familiar to me.

54:23.640 --> 54:29.370
-Are you sure you didn't call
Kyle's house after the murder?
-No, no, that wasn't me.

54:30.950 --> 54:33.550
Of course it wasn't.

54:36.450 --> 54:38.380
But, Michael,

54:38.390 --> 54:41.600
if you are anything
but the class misfit,

54:41.590 --> 54:44.150
which I know must give you
a lot of pain,

54:44.160 --> 54:47.490
I'm gonna find out
about it, you understand?

54:49.500 --> 54:51.930
Take it easy.

54:59.440 --> 55:01.170
He's a very sad boy.

55:01.180 --> 55:03.080
Maybe, but somethin's there.

55:03.080 --> 55:03.670
Yeah, ashes.

55:03.680 --> 55:06.710
And he made the phone call.
Check with
the phone company.

55:06.720 --> 55:08.260
All right.
What's with the ashes?

55:08.250 --> 55:12.050
There were fresh ashes
in the fireplace.
It's summer.

55:12.050 --> 55:13.450
He was burning something.

55:13.460 --> 55:15.760
-I think we just got
very lucky.
-Maybe.

55:15.760 --> 55:20.720
-What the hell you doin'?
-I'm sick of you doin'
20 m.p.h. in this town.

55:20.730 --> 55:22.860
Gimme the keys.

55:43.820 --> 55:47.420
[CHEWING, MUNCHING]

55:48.960 --> 55:51.800
[HEAVY METAL MUSIC PLAYING]

55:55.400 --> 55:59.070
<i>♪ Dig, dig, dig for yourself</i>

55:59.070 --> 56:02.540
<i>♪ Dig, dig, dig for your soul</i>

56:02.540 --> 56:04.500
<i>♪ Dig, dig, dig... ♪</i>

56:04.510 --> 56:06.610
Slob.

56:07.080 --> 56:07.820
Hi, Mike.

56:07.810 --> 56:11.280
Fixed myself a little snack.
Hope you don't mind.

56:11.280 --> 56:13.610
[EXHALES]
They think it's me.

56:13.620 --> 56:15.490
Of course they do.

56:15.480 --> 56:17.550
Right now
Hayden only suspects you.

56:17.550 --> 56:22.350
How long you think it's
gonna be
before he has proof, huh?

56:22.360 --> 56:25.130
A few hours?
[SLURPS NOISILY]

56:25.130 --> 56:27.330
Few minutes, maybe.

56:27.460 --> 56:31.200
Tick-tock, tick-tock,
hey, Mike?

56:31.200 --> 56:33.430
You see today's paper?

56:40.040 --> 56:43.510
"Special edition."
Ooh!

56:45.810 --> 56:47.140
"Interview with best friend."

56:47.150 --> 56:50.750
"All of Mountview High
was in a state of shock."

56:50.750 --> 56:52.020
So on, so on, so on.

56:52.020 --> 56:56.390
"One student's loss
was greater..."
Mmm?

56:56.390 --> 56:58.460
"'I miss him. God.

56:58.460 --> 57:02.260
"'I miss him already,'
sobbed his best friend

57:02.260 --> 57:05.660
"and president
of the still-banned

57:05.670 --> 57:09.610
"Horror Club."

57:17.580 --> 57:19.940
How could she?

57:19.950 --> 57:22.410
Trust me, Michael.

57:22.420 --> 57:26.260
I only want what you want.

57:27.890 --> 57:29.650
Buddies forever?

57:29.660 --> 57:30.850
Damn you!

57:30.860 --> 57:33.260
[ZAPPING]

57:33.260 --> 57:34.590
Hold still!

57:34.600 --> 57:36.100
[GRUNTS]

57:36.100 --> 57:38.660
[GASPING]

57:39.700 --> 57:41.400
Scared of blood?

57:41.400 --> 57:44.270
Remind you of something?

57:46.140 --> 57:48.970
That road? The rain?

57:48.980 --> 57:50.220
Your mother?

57:50.210 --> 57:51.780
Let go of me.

58:02.190 --> 58:06.320
Play it, Michael.
Or forget all this.

58:06.330 --> 58:10.360
Join your mother.
Take your own life.

58:10.370 --> 58:13.470
You've thought of it
many times before.

58:13.470 --> 58:15.030
You could be with her forever.

58:15.040 --> 58:17.480
You started this, and
now you're afraid to
finish it,

58:17.470 --> 58:19.770
just like you're afraid
of everything else!

58:19.780 --> 58:21.080
Of Kimberly, of Fromberg,

58:21.080 --> 58:25.150
of telling your father
how sick you are of being
left alone all the time.

58:25.150 --> 58:28.060
Of your mother,
who abandoned you.

58:28.050 --> 58:32.680
I'm trying to help you!
But you won't let me.

58:33.260 --> 58:34.900
How?

58:38.730 --> 58:43.200
A bargain,
between friends.

58:43.200 --> 58:48.500
Play "Part Three,"
but you only need to remove
the clue.

58:48.500 --> 58:50.530
No killing.

58:50.540 --> 58:52.570
There's no clue.

58:52.570 --> 58:55.070
It's just a trick.

58:58.580 --> 59:01.080
You just don't trust me.

59:01.080 --> 59:03.680
[ZAPPING]

59:05.850 --> 59:06.420
[TV TURNS ON]

59:06.420 --> 59:11.290
-[ZAPPING]
-Wait a minute!
Come back! Hold on.

59:14.030 --> 59:17.630
How am I supposed to know
what the clue is?

59:17.730 --> 59:19.500
Friends?

59:20.070 --> 59:24.000
Yeah.
Sure. Friends.

59:24.010 --> 59:29.620
-Buddies.
Whatever you want.
-Footprint.

59:29.610 --> 59:31.110
What?

59:31.110 --> 59:31.810
Footprints in the mud.

59:31.810 --> 59:36.250
But where? That is the
question. Play it, Michael.
[FINGERNAILS SCRATCHING GLASS]

59:36.250 --> 59:40.380
Otherwise you'll never
remember the location.

59:42.060 --> 59:43.430
My limp.

59:43.430 --> 59:45.500
Excellent!

59:47.060 --> 59:48.730
There's no killing, right?

59:48.730 --> 59:54.100
Whatever happens is up to you.
But don't let your
time run out.

59:54.240 --> 59:55.880
If I do?

59:57.410 --> 01:00:01.680
Game over. You lose.

01:00:56.360 --> 01:00:58.830
[SCREAMING]

01:01:03.140 --> 01:01:05.140
[SCREAMING]

01:01:05.140 --> 01:01:08.210
[PANTING]

01:01:09.010 --> 01:01:10.910
[DOORBELL RINGS]

01:01:10.910 --> 01:01:12.480
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

01:01:12.480 --> 01:01:13.910
Michael?

01:01:19.350 --> 01:01:22.390
Michael, come on!

01:01:23.460 --> 01:01:25.720
Michael!

01:01:28.300 --> 01:01:33.910
Michael!
I need to talk to you.
We need to talk.

01:01:36.640 --> 01:01:41.440
Michael,
I have to talk to you.
We need to talk.

01:01:43.510 --> 01:01:50.180
Michael. I didn't mean
for this to happen.
Stacie did it.

01:01:50.350 --> 01:01:51.880
Michael, I'm so sorry.

01:01:51.890 --> 01:01:56.960
-I didn't mean...
[INDISTINCT]
-[HEAVY METAL MUSIC PLAYING]

01:02:06.230 --> 01:02:09.970
[MUSIC CONTINUES INDISTINCT]

01:03:04.160 --> 01:03:07.120
HAYDEN: May I have your
attention, please?

01:03:08.860 --> 01:03:11.060
Stay in pairs.

01:03:11.530 --> 01:03:14.660
One walkie-talkie
to a group.

01:03:14.670 --> 01:03:18.600
Hopefully this will be
an uneventful evening.

01:03:18.610 --> 01:03:21.950
You're here
to keep things calm,

01:03:22.040 --> 01:03:23.010
to protect.

01:03:23.010 --> 01:03:25.840
That's what a neighborhood
watch is all about.

01:03:25.850 --> 01:03:31.360
If you see anything unusual,
you come and report
directly to me.

01:03:32.250 --> 01:03:34.020
One last thing.

01:03:34.020 --> 01:03:36.250
I know you're volunteers.

01:03:36.260 --> 01:03:38.990
I know you're enthusiastic.

01:03:38.990 --> 01:03:40.090
Some more than others.

01:03:40.100 --> 01:03:45.140
And I know some of you
own hunting rifles
and revolvers.

01:03:45.500 --> 01:03:48.500
If I see a weapon
in a citizen's hands tonight,

01:03:48.500 --> 01:03:53.500
I'm gonna confiscate
that weapon, and I'm gonna
arrest that citizen,

01:03:53.510 --> 01:03:56.370
even if it's a water pistol.

01:03:56.540 --> 01:03:57.710
Clear?

01:03:57.710 --> 01:03:59.110
[MEN AGREEING]

01:03:59.110 --> 01:04:03.280
Okay, that's it.
Thank you for doing this.

01:04:07.790 --> 01:04:10.390
[BREATHING UNEVENLY]

01:04:10.990 --> 01:04:14.090
All right.
Here goes nothin'.

01:04:20.140 --> 01:04:24.910
Just a clue.
No more killing.
Just the clue.

01:04:26.640 --> 01:04:30.640
[TV TURNS ON]

01:04:41.490 --> 01:04:46.560
[PANTING]

01:04:59.980 --> 01:05:02.480
[GRUNTING]

01:05:11.290 --> 01:05:13.360
[PHONE RINGS]

01:05:18.730 --> 01:05:19.170
Yeah.

01:05:19.160 --> 01:05:24.030
TRICKSTER:
I believe there's
an intruder in your yard.

01:05:24.730 --> 01:05:26.630
Who's this?

01:05:26.630 --> 01:05:29.130
A concerned citizen.

01:05:29.140 --> 01:05:31.310
Who is this?

01:05:31.910 --> 01:05:34.110
[EXHALES]

01:05:36.140 --> 01:05:37.670
[PANTING]

01:05:37.680 --> 01:05:39.310
Hey!

01:05:42.780 --> 01:05:45.150
[GRUNTING]

01:05:51.830 --> 01:05:54.230
[GASPING]

01:05:54.230 --> 01:05:57.790
Here you go, man.
[LAUGHING]

01:05:58.670 --> 01:06:01.670
[PANTING]

01:06:02.570 --> 01:06:04.200
[DOG BARKING]

01:06:04.210 --> 01:06:06.910
[MEN'S VOICES INDISTINCT]

01:06:08.540 --> 01:06:13.110
-[DOG BARKING]
-MAN: That's it.
That's it. This way.

01:06:16.120 --> 01:06:18.490
MAN: Over here.
More light.

01:06:18.720 --> 01:06:23.220
-Shoot!
-[DISPATCHER ON RADIO,
INDISTINCT]

01:06:23.220 --> 01:06:25.760
[PANTING]

01:06:30.000 --> 01:06:32.360
[BOTTLE BREAKING]

01:06:33.440 --> 01:06:36.580
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

01:07:07.170 --> 01:07:09.600
[BRANCH SNAPS]

01:07:18.710 --> 01:07:21.640
[CHITTERING]

01:07:36.300 --> 01:07:40.070
[DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

01:07:53.010 --> 01:07:54.310
Ahhh!

01:07:54.320 --> 01:07:55.290
Got you!

01:07:55.280 --> 01:07:58.110
Lemme go!
Lemme go!

01:07:58.120 --> 01:08:03.820
MAN: Hayden!
Hayden, where the hell are ya?
I got him here! Hayden!

01:08:03.830 --> 01:08:05.400
Hayden.
What is it?

01:08:05.390 --> 01:08:05.990
[STATIC]
Hayden!

01:08:05.990 --> 01:08:10.790
-Hayden, Hayden!
-Turn the knob on the top
of the radio, the small one.

01:08:10.800 --> 01:08:15.200
Hayden, come in
for god's sake!
[SCREAMS]

01:08:18.439 --> 01:08:19.800
HAYDEN: <i> Fromberg,</i>
<i>are you there?</i>

01:08:19.810 --> 01:08:23.279
-MICHAEL: Oh, jeez.
-HAYDEN: <i> Can you hear me?</i>
<i>Come in.</i>

01:08:23.279 --> 01:08:24.970
SEARCHER:
What was that?

01:08:24.979 --> 01:08:26.710
Hey, you!

01:08:27.479 --> 01:08:30.850
HAYDEN:
<i>Are you there?</i>

01:08:33.420 --> 01:08:36.450
MAN: Over there!
SEARCHER: Let's go!

01:08:39.760 --> 01:08:42.160
SEARCHER:
This way, come on!

01:08:42.160 --> 01:08:44.930
Let's go. Hurry up!

01:08:47.140 --> 01:08:48.640
Damn.

01:08:59.279 --> 01:09:01.840
[SHOUTING INDISTINCT]

01:09:04.819 --> 01:09:08.890
MAN: Hey, I need some light
over here. Right down there.

01:09:08.890 --> 01:09:11.390
[WHINING]

01:09:38.319 --> 01:09:39.950
[WHINES]

01:09:39.950 --> 01:09:41.020
[PANTING]

01:09:41.020 --> 01:09:46.660
[WHISPERING] Oh, God.
Okay, I know I said I'd never
ask you for anything again,

01:09:46.660 --> 01:09:48.990
but this time I really
mean it.

01:09:49.000 --> 01:09:51.540
Just leave me alone, please?

01:09:51.529 --> 01:09:53.560
Get outta here.

01:09:53.569 --> 01:09:55.930
[GROWLS SOFTLY]

01:10:04.050 --> 01:10:06.390
-MAN: Jeez.
-SEARCHER:
He's got a gun!

01:10:06.380 --> 01:10:08.380
MARTIN:
Police officer.

01:10:08.380 --> 01:10:11.180
[MARTIN CHOKING]

01:10:32.910 --> 01:10:35.820
[SIREN WAILING]

01:10:57.630 --> 01:11:00.360
What are ya doin', kid?
[SCREAMS]

01:11:01.200 --> 01:11:02.130
I was... I...

01:11:02.140 --> 01:11:07.550
They just shot the killer
over there. Get outta here.

01:11:14.150 --> 01:11:17.710
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

01:11:32.170 --> 01:11:35.680
Which one of you would
like to tell his wife?

01:11:49.480 --> 01:11:50.850
Michael?

01:11:52.150 --> 01:11:54.280
What's going on?

01:11:55.520 --> 01:11:58.350
Are... Are you okay?

01:12:16.740 --> 01:12:18.410
[ZAPPING]

01:12:18.410 --> 01:12:21.240
Shoot!
What happened?

01:12:21.250 --> 01:12:25.520
<i>You made it, Michael.</i>
<i>A bit clumsy, but you made it!</i>

01:12:25.520 --> 01:12:29.990
I killed somebody.
Again. I killed somebody.

01:12:29.990 --> 01:12:34.160
<i>Actually...</i>
<i>You were magnificent!</i>

01:12:34.160 --> 01:12:36.030
<i>The neighborhood</i>
<i>is covered in blood.</i>

01:12:36.030 --> 01:12:39.300
But you said
I wouldn't kill anybody.
You promised!

01:12:39.300 --> 01:12:43.200
<i>You protected yourself.</i>
<i>Your hand was forced.</i>
<i>You had no choice.</i>

01:12:43.200 --> 01:12:49.510
<i>Michael. Michael!</i>
[SCREAMING,
NAILS SCRAPING GLASS]

01:12:50.410 --> 01:12:53.680
<i>Now that I have</i>
<i>your attention...</i>

01:12:53.680 --> 01:12:55.580
[ZAPPING]

01:12:55.580 --> 01:12:57.350
Stop.

01:12:57.350 --> 01:13:00.480
This isn't a game anymore.

01:13:00.490 --> 01:13:03.090
This is crime. This is
just lots of crimes!

01:13:03.090 --> 01:13:06.320
<i>It's only a crime</i>
<i>if you get caught.</i>

01:13:06.330 --> 01:13:08.840
<i>There was a witness,</i>

01:13:08.830 --> 01:13:12.260
<i>and you know who she is.</i>

01:13:25.580 --> 01:13:27.680
No.

01:13:27.750 --> 01:13:30.410
<i>"Part Four."</i>

01:13:35.060 --> 01:13:37.200
[ZAPPING]

01:13:54.110 --> 01:13:57.540
Forensics says
you're gonna need this.

01:13:57.550 --> 01:14:02.050
And the Brower kid
is the one
who placed the call.

01:14:18.030 --> 01:14:23.130
[NAILS CLICKING ON GLASS]
<i>Talk to me.</i>

01:14:38.450 --> 01:14:40.580
What do you want from me?

01:14:40.590 --> 01:14:43.690
<i>You know who the witness is,</i>
<i>don't you?</i>

01:14:43.690 --> 01:14:47.290
<i>And you know</i>
<i>what has to be done.</i>

01:14:51.200 --> 01:14:53.930
<i>"Part Four."</i>

01:14:53.940 --> 01:14:56.610
That's it.

01:14:56.600 --> 01:15:00.170
I'm gonna go to Hayden
right now

01:15:00.170 --> 01:15:02.770
and turn myself in.

01:15:05.980 --> 01:15:08.440
[ZAPPING]

01:15:10.820 --> 01:15:14.320
You wanted the ultimate
experience in terror.

01:15:14.320 --> 01:15:16.020
Well, terror's in the doing.

01:15:16.020 --> 01:15:18.350
It's not watching horror films
like some child.

01:15:18.360 --> 01:15:23.430
And it's not spying on
Kimberly.
You get off on that, Michael.

01:15:23.430 --> 01:15:24.030
I love her.

01:15:24.030 --> 01:15:26.230
It could be any girl
in any window.

01:15:26.230 --> 01:15:27.660
I won't kill her!

01:15:27.670 --> 01:15:28.500
She'll tell!

01:15:28.500 --> 01:15:31.130
She won't tell!
She'll come to me first!

01:15:31.140 --> 01:15:32.100
Like last time?

01:15:32.110 --> 01:15:32.780
Stop this!

01:15:32.770 --> 01:15:37.510
Only you can stop this.
Her life or yours!

01:15:37.510 --> 01:15:39.110
Choose.

01:15:40.650 --> 01:15:43.380
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

01:15:44.720 --> 01:15:46.620
Cut.

01:15:46.950 --> 01:15:49.450
[ZAPPING]

01:16:05.940 --> 01:16:08.340
[DOORBELL RINGS]

01:16:14.080 --> 01:16:16.350
[RINGS]

01:16:19.450 --> 01:16:21.150
Michael?

01:16:22.320 --> 01:16:24.620
KIMBERLY: Michael?

